      <lg xml:id="TolE0179">
<l>nīye ṉorupeyar neṭumutal kuṟuku</l>
<l>māvayi ṉakara moṟṟā kummē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The scholars say</l>
<l>that the ending <foreign xml:lang="ta">ai</foreign> of the interrogative <foreign xml:lang="ta">yā</foreign>, too,</l>
<l>will not fail to observe that rule ;<note
              place="foot">I.e. takes<foreign xml:lang="ta">vaṟṟu</foreign> before case-marker.</note></l>
<l>the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">v</foreign> disappears there with <foreign xml:lang="ta">ai</foreign>.<note
              place="foot">I.e. <foreign xml:lang="ta">-v-ai</foreign> of <foreign xml:lang="ta">yā-vai</foreign> is dropped : <foreign xml:lang="ta">yāvai + ai &gt; yā-vaṟṟ-ai.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
